					<p>The past 35 years of biotech development have introduced a number of &quot;tremendous applications,&quot; particularly in the area of bioengineered drugs, Drew Endy said. Research is now moving ahead at a rapid clip, with &quot;geometric improvements&quot; in tools used to construct DNA from scratch, he observed. Endy states that an open technology platform &quot;where the genetic componentry is available for anybody who might want to start a biotechnology company&quot; is critical to advancing the field. (Source: AFP, 14 February 2009)</p>
